\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy serves as the unifying ethos that aligns individual conduct with the organizational mission —
 defining how the Department leads,
 operates,
 and serves.
 The standards established here complement the ethical obligations defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Code of Ethics and Professional Conduct) and operationalize the professional discipline required to sustain the Department's governance,
 security,
 and service delivery mission.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Operational Authority and Autonomy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Information Operations Department shall maintain operational authority over the administration,
 security,
 architecture,
 and configuration of all Elko County information systems,
 infrastructure,
 and technology assets placed under the governance of the Information Operations Department as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (IT Governance and Oversight Structure).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Unified Authority
\series default
:
 To support compliance with the strict connectivity and security requirements of the 
\series bold
CJIS
\series default
 Security Policy v6.0 Appendix D.2 (Management Control Agreement),
 Elko County has adopted a unified governance structure for shared infrastructure.
 Under this structure,
 the IT Director retains final decision-making authority over all technical controls and risk mitigation strategies across the enterprise,
 subject to the statutory management control authority of each 
\series bold
Criminal Justice Agency (CJA)
\series default
 over CJIS data policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Independence
\series default
:
 While administratively reporting to County Management,
 the Department's operational decisions shall be driven by technical standards,
 security mandates,
 and risk assessments.
 Mandatory security controls,
 engineering standards,
 and the ethical obligations established under 
\series bold
NRS
\series default
 281A.400 (Code of Ethical Standards) shall take precedence over political pressure or external influence.
 Technical decisions shall be made in accordance with the delegation framework defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Chain of Command and Escalation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The chain of command is a mechanism for accountability and risk management.
 All Information Operations Personnel shall utilize the chain of command to ensure decisions are made at the appropriate authority level.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Act Decisively
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall execute duties with precision within their assigned scope of authority.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Escalate with Purpose
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall escalate issues to their direct supervisor within one (1) business day when operational risk,
 legal constraints,
 or policy ambiguity exceed their defined authority or expertise.
 During active incidents,
 personnel shall escalate in accordance with the incident response escalation procedures defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Incident Response Policy Overview).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Unified Direction
\series default
:
 Once a decision is made by the designated authority,
 all Information Operations Personnel shall implement that decision promptly.
 Concerns about implementation shall be raised through the escalation process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 without impeding execution unless a safety or legal issue is identified.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Leadership and Crisis Management
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Leadership within the Information Operations Department is defined by consistency,
 clarity,
 and accountability.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Communicate with Precision
\series default
:
 The IT Director and Assistant IT Director shall issue instructions and status reports that are clear,
 specific,
 and actionable.
 All Information Operations Personnel shall confirm understanding of critical directives before execution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Decide Based on Standards
\series default
:
 The IT Director and Assistant IT Director shall base operational decisions on data,
 policy,
 and formal risk assessment.
 Technical standards and mandatory security controls shall take precedence over political pressure,
 personal sentiment,
 or external influence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Accountability
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director and Assistant IT Director shall acknowledge errors transparently.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director and Assistant IT Director shall document lessons learned within five (5) business days of incident closure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall ensure remediation actions are tracked to completion in the Department's system of record.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Crisis Discipline
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
During major incidents,
 all Information Operations Personnel shall adhere to the incident response protocols defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
During major incidents,
 the IT Director and Assistant IT Director shall provide clear,
 evidence-based direction to maintain operational discipline.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director and Assistant IT Director shall participate in formal post-incident reviews to document lessons learned.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Operational Discipline
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Operational discipline is the foundation of the Department's credibility.
 All Information Operations Personnel shall execute duties according to the following standards:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Own the Scope
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall fully own tasks within their job role.
 If a task falls outside their scope,
 they shall escalate it with clear context and documentation rather than ignoring it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Document as Standard
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall document operational actions,
 changes,
 and decisions in accordance with the documentation requirements established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prioritize Based on Risk
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall assess urgency based on impact to County operations and security,
 not solely on the volume of the request.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Resolve or Escalate
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall actively move every ticket or work order toward resolution or escalate it to the appropriate tier with sufficient context for action.
 No ticket or work order shall remain without a documented status update beyond the timeframes established in the applicable service level targets.
\end_layout

